A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To create and provide for a task force to study the minimum foundation program formula
and recommend permanent, predictable funding for pay raises for teachers and
support staff.
WHEREAS, the Revenue Estimating Conference has recently reduced the official
state revenue forecast, projecting significant declines in anticipated collections for the
current and upcoming fiscal year, thereby increasing pressure on the state budget and
limiting the availability of recurring revenues; and
WHEREAS, in response to these fiscal challenges, since 2024, the legislature and
the governor have demonstrated a consistent commitment to responsible budgeting practices,
including not using nonrecurring revenue for recurring expenses and avoiding structural
deficits that could jeopardize long-term fiscal stability; and
WHEREAS, Governor Jeff Landry has instructed the legislature to find a source of
funding for permanent, predictable pay raises for teachers that will be durable across
changing fiscal conditions; and
WHEREAS, the use of one-time funding sources to support ongoing obligations is
prohibited by Article VII, Section 10 of the Constitution of Louisiana, and is particularly
problematic when applied to recurring expenses such as employee compensation; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Constitution also restricts the use of the Revenue
Stabilization Fund to limited purposes, including capital outlay, transportation infrastructure,
and certain declared emergencies, and does not authorize its use as a recurring funding
source for ongoing expenditures such as salaries or stipends; and
WHEREAS, because compensation for teachers and support staff constitutes a
recurring obligation, reliance on the Revenue Stabilization Fund or any other nonrecurring
source to fund such compensation would be inconsistent with constitutional limitations and
