(4) Student count methodology and timing, including the practical impacts of count
dates on school systems and enrollment volatility during the year.
(5) Transparency and accountability mechanisms, including the operation of the 70%
expenditure requirement and how school systems classify and report expenditures to ensure
state funding reaches classrooms and employee paychecks.
(6) Potential permanent and recurring funding mechanisms that comply with
constitutional and fiscal constraints and that align with the state's commitment to limiting
the use of nonrecurring revenue for recurring obligations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
members:
(1) The president of the Senate, or his designee, who shall serve as chair.
(2) The speaker of the House of Representatives, or his designee.
(3) The chairman of the Senate Committee on Finance, or his designee.
(4) The chairman of the House Committee on Appropriations, or his designee.
(5) The chairman of the Senate Committee on Education, or his designee.
(6) The chairman of the House Committee on Education, or his designee.
(7) The chairman of the Senate Republican Legislative Delegation, or his designee.
(8) The chairman of the Senate Democratic Legislative Delegation, or his designee.
(9) The chairman of the House Republican Legislative Delegation, or his designee.
(10) The chairman of the House Democratic Legislative Delegation, or his designee.
(11) The governor of Louisiana, or his designee.
(12) The president of the Louisiana Federation of Teachers, or his designee.
(13) The president of the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education, or his
designee.
(14) The executive director of the Louisiana School Boards Association, or his
designee.
(15) The executive director of the Louisiana Association of School Superintendents
and Administrators, or his designee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall solicit information from
classroom teachers, support staff, local school board members, superintendents, school
