business officials, BESE, the state Department of Education, Louisiana public charter school
leaders, the business community, and other stakeholders deemed appropriate by the chair.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Legislative Auditor is hereby requested to
examine and review the books and accounts of local public school systems to evaluate
compliance with the 70% expenditure requirement in the areas of instruction and school
administration at the school building level as required by the MFP, to make
recommendations to ensure that state funding is used uniformly and effectively for
instruction and employee compensation, to present its findings to the task force, and to assist
with additional matters related to the MFP as may be requested by the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that each appointing or designating authority shall
submit the name of each appointee or designee to the secretary of the Senate no later than
July 1, 2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene at the call of the
chair and may elect any other officer it deems appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force shall constitute a
quorum, and official action shall require the affirmative vote of a majority of the members.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
without compensation, except per diem or expense reimbursement to which they may be
individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall terminate on the date of the
submission of its report or January 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
office of the governor, the president of the Louisiana Federation of Teachers, the president
of the State Board of Elementary and Secondary Education, the executive director of the
Louisiana School Boards Association, the Louisiana Legislative Auditor, and the executive
director of the Louisiana Association of School Superintendents and Administrators.
